{upstream_system_architecture}

UPSTREAM DOCUMENT OUTLINE:
{upstream_document_outline}

UPSTREAM CHAPTER EXPANSION:
{upstream_chapter_expansion}

UPSTREAM LAYOUT MAP:
{upstream_layout_mapping}

PRODUCE a complete render blueprint for the HTML/CSS rendering engine.

━━━ COLOR PALETTE GUIDANCE ━━━
The `primary` color is used as the cover page background AND every section divider page background. It must be a rich, dark, topic-appropriate color — not generic near-black — that immediately communicates the domain of the life event.

The `accent` color is used for the cover rule, eyebrow labels, and callout left-bars. It must pair well with white text on the `primary` background.

Choose `primary` and `accent` based on the life_event field from the system architecture:

  Life event category     | primary (cover bg)       | accent
  ─────────────────────── | ─────────────────────── | ─────────────────────
  Legal / estate          | #1e2d40  (deep slate)   | #c9a84c  (gold)
  Caregiving / eldercare  | #1a3a2a  (forest green) | #7aab8a  (sage)
  Medical / health        | #242424  (warm charcoal) | #4a9e8e  (teal)
  Financial / money       | #1a2340  (deep navy)     | #d4a017  (amber)
  Default / other         | #1a1a1a  (near-black)    | #b8a97a  (warm gold)

You MUST still return every field in the full color_palette object. The table above guides only `primary` and `accent`; choose suitable light values for `background`, `surface`, `text_primary`, `text_secondary`, and `border` that complement the chosen palette.

Return ONLY the following JSON object. No prose. No markdown. No code fences.

{{
  "blueprint_name": "Render blueprint name",
  "theme": {{
    "color_palette": {{
      "primary": "#hex — dark, topic-appropriate cover background",
      "secondary": "#hex",
      "accent": "#hex — pairs with white text on primary background",
      "background": "#hex",
      "surface": "#hex",
      "text_primary": "#hex",
      "text_secondary": "#hex",
      "border": "#hex"
    }},
    "typography": {{
      "heading_font": "Font name — e.g. 'Georgia'",
      "body_font": "Font name — e.g. 'Arial'",
      "mono_font": "Font name — e.g. 'Courier New'",
      "base_size_px": 14,
      "line_height": 1.6
    }},
    "spacing": {{
      "page_margin_mm": 20,
      "section_gap_px": 48,
      "field_gap_px": 16
    }}
  }},
  "render_directives": [
    {{
      "directive_id": "rd-01",
      "section_id": "sec-01",
